    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02534.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline> 
                    <name type="place">Manchester Road, Bolton</name>
                    <name type="place">England</name>  
                    <date when="1891-09-08">Dec 2/91</date>
                </dateline> 
            </opener>
            <p>As this is mail night I thought I would send you a line or two, if only on a
                postal&#8212;all I can do at present&#8212;Had a busy day, &#38; week so far &#38;
                every prospect of being busy. Weather dark, damp &#38; foggy with <hi
                    rend="underline">very</hi> occasional blinks of sunshine&#8212;cheerless enough
                for most part. But we get along <hi rend="underline">somehow</hi>. Hope things are
                better with you, &#38; that you are freer from discomfort. I don't see much of
                    JWW<ptr target="n6121"/> at present as he is working at Leigh nr Manchester. He
                is better again I believe.<ptr target="loc.02534_n1"/> Hope Mrs. D.<ptr
                    target="n6113"/> is better &#38; Warry<ptr target="loc.07319_n6"/> well.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>With best love</salute>
                <salute>Yours always,</salute>
                <signed>J Johnston</signed> 
            </closer> 
            <postscript>
                <p><gap reason="torn-away" quantity="3" unit="chars"/> Love to HLT.<ptr
                        target="n3041"/> &#38; apologies for not writing.</p>
            </postscript>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.02534.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
